description: 2002 Mastercraft Prostar 209 Sammy Duval Limited Edition 310HP Indmar Predator fuel injected 5.7 liter Chevrolet Vortec engine. 125000.00 negotiable. Needs some TLC I don't have a shop this winter to work on the boat, and I think I'm going to abandon the boat ownership world for awhile. The boat was bought as a project. In December 2012, The boat had saltwater history, and an accident where the previous owner ran into something, therefore the gel has spider web cracks in the surface of the bow. There are also spiderweb cracks around some of the cover snap holes I removed and where the guide pole hit the boat. New re-manufactured marine engine long block, fall of 2014 currently less than 125hrs on it. Spare prop needs refurbished. 1000.00 Tower Bimini cover.. New starter this year. Crucial spare part collection, dash, gauges, fuel pump, and other spares, bits and pieces, I have collected from a donor boat that had low hours and no saltwater history Cosmetically the hull is a bit rough, I removed all the snaps that held the previous cover on, The snap holes need filled. There are alot of spideweb cracks in the gel, the graphics/stickers are shot, it could use a gelcoat refresh top to bottom. It isn't necessary though just ugly. The rub rail has a break in it due to a cold storage accident, where someone ran into the guide post and it broke broke a small chunk of the rub rail. it is all repairable but will take time and a decent work space, Otherwise the boat looks great 30 feet away. Interior is ugly but not too many holes tears and stains that would require an immediate replacement. The drivers seat and observer seat are in great condition. It has some electrical issues, occasionally the pressure and temp gauges wont activate, I just cycle the key until they do. It's probably related to saltwater corrosion and a bad ground in the harness. I have a freshwater harness from a boat that spent its life in Indiana so I'm pretty sure the harness swap will cure this. I have an entire dash assembly from the same year Prostar so the parts are there to make this nice and reliable. Trailer needs a paint job, the brakes work, I put a new strap on the the winch last season. One brand new tire and one, one year old tire. There is a little fender rash from Don's Scratch and Storage facility. It would be an easy fix. Needs throttle cable and steering cable. I have spares, just haven't installed them. OEM New Dimension tower has a crack in it. It came from the previous owner like that. I called the builder and he can fix it. I put off sending it in to see if I could find a better fix. Three years later the crack hasn't shown any signs of growing. Cover needs repaired or replaced. This is a great running and driving ski boat that works best as a wakeboard tractor, it will throw a decent sized wake to surf, and isn't bad at slalom and barefooting. This boat runs as well as it did when new, and only needs a good winters worth of work to sort the little things out. do NOT contact me with unsolicited services or offers
title: 2002 Mastercraft Prostar 209 Sammy Duval LTD
